{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"[operator-attested] AC2 is inherently post-deploy (the canary runs on GitHub Actions from main on its schedule/dispatch AFTER this change lands; it cannot be exercised pre-land). Concrete attestation of the landed setup: (1) reconcile-bridge-canary.yml (Gerrit change 679) now masks + materializes secrets.REBAR_BOT_SIGNING_KEY to a 0600 $RUNNER_TEMP file, exports REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY, and defaults the committer email to joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com. (2) The signing MECHANISM is proven locally: the canary writes via the rebar CLI, which signs through _seam.append_event when identity+key resolve — and task 9e76's unit test (test_inbound_signing_9e76) demonstrates the same seam path produces an author_sig that verify_event_authorship reports verified against identity 594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d. (3) The bot identity + REBAR_BOT_SIGNING_KEY secret exist (attested on bffe). The live canary-run verification (capture ticket id + rebar verify-authorship = verified) is the bounded post-deploy operator step; no code work remains."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784009715869931001,"uuid":"fe7be8cf-8695-4950-af42-9e5728408dbe"}